summary: 03/16/1993: Djilali Liabes, a former Algerian Education Minister was shot to death by extremists as he left his home. This attack was apart of a multiple incident see event ID#'s 199303140001, 199303160001, and 199303170002 for more information.
addnotes: One casualty and no injuries resulted from the attack. See event ID 199303140001 for more information on multiple attacks against Algerian government officials in the month of March.
scite1: Rachid Khiari, “New Slaying of High-Ranking Official as Terror Wave Continues,” The Associated Press, March 17, 1993.
scite3: “Algerian terrorism mounts; top government adviser slain,” Chicago Tribune, March 18, 1993.
